  33. ‌let rec select_addr = function
  34.   | Cop((Caddi | Cadda | Caddv), [arg; Cconst_int (m, _)], _) ->
  35.       let (a, n) = select_addr arg in (a, n + m)
  36.   | Cop((Caddi | Cadda | Caddv), [Cconst_int (m, _); arg], _) ->
  37.       let (a, n) = select_addr arg in (a, n + m)
  38.   | Cop((Caddi | Cadda | Caddv), [arg1; arg2], _) ->
  39.       begin match (select_addr arg1, select_addr arg2) with
  40.           ((Alinear e1, n1), (Alinear e2, n2)) ->
  41.               (Aadd(e1, e2), n1 + n2)
  42.         | _ ->
  43.               (Aadd(arg1, arg2), 0)
  44.       end
  45.   | exp ->
  46.       (Alinear exp, 0)

  50. ‌let pseudoregs_for_operation op arg res =
  51.   match op with
  52.   (* Two-address binary operations: arg.(0) and res.(0) must be the same *)
  53.   | Iintop(Iadd|Isub|Imul|Iand|Ior|Ixor)  | Iaddf|Isubf|Imulf|Idivf ->
  54.       ([|res.(0); arg.(1)|], res)
  55.   | Ispecific _ ->
  56.     ( [| arg.(0); arg.(1); res.(0) |], [| res.(0) |])
  57.   (* One-address unary operations: arg.(0) and res.(0) must be the same *)
  58.   |  Iintop_imm((Imul|Iand|Ior|Ixor), _) -> (res, res)
  59.   (* Other instructions are regular *)
  60.   | _ -> raise Use_default

  62. ‌let is_immediate n = n <= 0x7FFF_FFFF && n >= -0x8000_0000
  63. ‌let is_immediate_logical n = n <= 0xFFFF_FFFF && n >= 0

  65. class selector = object (self)

  67. inherit Selectgen.selector_generic as super

  69. method is_immediate_test cmp n =
  70.   match cmp with
  71.   | Isigned _ -> is_immediate n
  72.   | Iunsigned _ -> is_immediate_logical n

  74. method! is_immediate op n =
  75.   match op with
  76.   | Iadd | Imul -> is_immediate n
  77.   | Isub -> is_immediate (-n)
  78.   | Iand -> n <= -1 && n >= -0x1_0000_0000
  79.   | Ior | Ixor -> is_immediate_logical n
  80.   | Icomp c -> self#is_immediate_test c n
  81.   | Icheckbound -> is_immediate_logical n (* unsigned comparison *)
  82.   | _ -> super#is_immediate op n

  84. method select_addressing _chunk exp =
  85.   let (a, d) = select_addr exp in
  86.   (* 20-bit signed displacement *)
  87.   if d < 0x80000 && d >= -0x80000 then begin
  88.     match a with
  89.     | Alinear e -> (Iindexed d, e)
  90.     | Aadd(e1, e2) -> (Iindexed2 d, Ctuple [e1; e2])
  91.   end else
  92.     (Iindexed 0, exp)

  94. method! select_operation op args dbg =
  95.   match (op, args) with
  96.   (* Recognize mult-add and mult-sub instructions *)
  97.   | (Caddf, [Cop(Cmulf, [arg1; arg2], _); arg3]) ->
  98.       (Ispecific Imultaddf, [arg1; arg2; arg3])
  99.   | (Caddf, [arg3; Cop(Cmulf, [arg1; arg2], _)]) ->
  100.       (Ispecific Imultaddf, [arg1; arg2; arg3])
  101.   | (Csubf, [Cop(Cmulf, [arg1; arg2], _); arg3]) ->
  102.       (Ispecific Imultsubf, [arg1; arg2; arg3])
  103.   | _ ->
  104.       super#select_operation op args dbg

  106. method! insert_op_debug env op dbg rs rd =
  107.   try
  108. ‌    let (rsrc, rdst) = pseudoregs_for_operation op rs rd in
  109.     self#insert_moves env rs rsrc;
  110.     self#insert_debug env (Iop op) dbg rsrc rdst;
  111.     self#insert_moves env rdst rd;
  112.     rd
  113.   with Use_default ->
  114.     super#insert_op_debug env op dbg rs rd

  116. end

  118. ‌let fundecl ~future_funcnames f =
  119.   (new selector)#emit_fundecl ~future_funcnames f
